briefdescription.para: get_hw_platform is a helper function which reads the underlying and returns platform type. This is used buring system initialization load driver modules for corresponding platforms.

simplesect.para: function retruns platform type defined in enum platform_t.

briefdescription.para: fapi_eth_init performs system initialization based on underlying . This is called during system initialization by eth_sl load driver modules for underlying platforms.
fapi_eth_uninit performs un initialization of ethernet driver modules \ based on underlying hardware
fapi_sys_set configures the struct sys_cfg_t and fills in initialization \ parameters
fapi_sys_get retrieves data in struct sys_cfg_t
fapi_sys_if_attach adds interface specified in struct ifcfg_t to PPA acceleration
fapi_sys_if_dettach deletes interface specified in struct ifcfg_t from PPA acceleration
fapi_sys_ppa_init performs configurations in PPA to prepare and intitialize PPA
fapi_sys_ppa_uninit performs configurations in PPA to unintitialize PPA
fapi_sys_ppa_enable enables or disable LAN and WAN acceleration in PPA

parameterdescription.para: and wan enable info by updating PPA_CMD_ENABLE_INFO structure

briefdescription.para: fapi_get_mac_addr reads mac address configured on system in /proc/cmdline returns the mac address. this is used during system initialization configure mac address of LAN and WAN interfaces.

simplesect.para: function retruns UGW_SUCCESS or UGW_FAILURE and returns mac address

briefdescription.para: fapi to find whether the linkenable is true/false.(Platform specific based on primary wan if only 1 wanmode supported)

parameterdescription.para: enable value from interface.cfg.Link enable modified if any platform dependency.

briefdescription.para: fapi_get_port reads the interface and returns port id of the interface reading from PPA_CMD_GET_PORTID ioctl

parameterdescription.para: name to be populated in intfPortMap_t struct id is available in intfPortMap_t

simplesect.para: function retruns port number or UGW_FAILURE

fapi_port_setstatus enables or disables switch port
fapi_port_setbitrate sets port bitrate on switch port provided

parameterdescription.para: port id, Max Bitrate to be configured(10,100,1000 Mbps)

briefdescription.para: fapi_port_setDuplexMode configures the switch port Duplex Mode provided

parameterdescription.para: port id, DuplexMode; Full Duplex or Half Duplex

briefdescription.para: fapi_port_getDuplexMode retrieves switch port Duplex Mode

parameterdescription.para: Duplex mode filled in struct PORTcfg_t

briefdescription.para: fapi_port_getbitrate retrieves switch port bitrate
fapi_port_getstatus retrieves switch port enable or disable status
fapi_rmon_get retrieves switch port RMON statistics
fapi_EnablePortMirror configures required switch parameters to setup port mirroring on the device. Fapi accepts interface names as inputs and sets up portmirroring for the corresponding ports.
fapi_DisablePortMirror configures required switch parameters to disable port mirroring on the device. Fapi accepts interface names as inputs and disables portmirroring for the corresponding ports.
fapi_switch_init performs configuration to initialize flow15 switch on xRX300 platforms
fapi_switch_uninit performs configuration to uninitialize flow15 switch on xRX300 platforms
fapi_vlan_config configures vlanid provided by user
platform_FapiReg registers fapi callback functions for platform it is defined for.
check loaded modules is a helper function which checks and returns success if module is already loaded returns failure if module is not already loaded/
fapi_sys_SWO is used when wan modes are swithched. this fapi handles unloading of drivers for old wan mode and loading of drivers for new wan mode and also initializes PPA

parameterdescription.para: wan mode information in sys_cfg_t structure
